obo:BFO_0000066  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_2421  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Electrophysiological analysis of evoked synaptic currents in CACNAB4 KO animals in somatosensroy thalamic neurons. A strong parallel decrease in both NMDA and non-NMDA components strongly implies a defect which is presynaptic in origin. The absence of an impact on inhibitory transmission suggests it is not related AP waveform changes.\n\n8/2/2018 Pim\n- Literal: \"We found a similar decrease in glutamatergic but not GABAergic responses in Cacna1atg homozygotes, suggesting that the independent mutations in the two strains each affected P/Q channel function by causing defective neurotransmitter release specific to glutamatergic synapses in the somatosensory thalamus.. Experimental description: Methods:\nMouse colonies\nColonies of Cacnb4lh homozygotes and their nonepileptic background\ncontrol strain [designated 1/1: descended from (C57BL/\n6JEi 3 C3H/HeSnJ) F1s] were maintained in the Duke University\nvivarium. Male lethargic heterozygotes (Cacnb4lh/1) were bred with\nfemale lethargic heterozygotes to produce 25% homozygous Cacnb4lh\nin the progeny" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" ;
        dc:date           "2018-08-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_2421" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

